Objectives:

  • Create interactive data visualisation by using functions provided by ggiraph and plotlyr packages

Getting Started

Installing the required libraries

pacman::p_load(ggiraph, plotly, 
               patchwork, DT, tidyverse)

Importing the Data

exam_data <- read_csv("data/Exam_data.csv")

To create an interactive version of ggplot2 geom (i.e. [geom_dotplot_interactive()] we first need to create the basic graph. Then, girafe() will be used to generate an svg object to be displayed on an html page.
